Preimplantation genetic screening in a case of recurrent trisomy 21 offspring. To describe a unique case of recurrent aneuploidy and the use of preimplantation genetic screening (PGS).Case report.Midwest academic medical center.A 36-year-old woman with two trisomy 21 offspring.Preimplantation genetic screening.Karyotype of embryos, liveborn eukaryotic infant.Preimplantation genetic screening was performed on three cryopreserved embryos, followed by a two-embryo transfer yielding a eukaryotic infant.Preimplantation genetic screening may prove to be useful as a diagnostic tool to help ensure a euploid pregnancy when termination is not a viable option for a couple.